        "headline": "Flood Warning issued June 7 at 9:59PM CDT until June 8 at 5:09PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX",
        "description": "...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Texas...\n\nSouth Fork Sabine River Near Quinlan affecting Hunt and Rockwall\nCounties.\n\nFor the South Fork Sabine River...including Quinlan...Minor flooding\nis forecast.\n\n* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.\n\n* WHERE...South Fork Sabine River near Quinlan.\n\n* WHEN...Until Monday afternoon.\n\n* IMPACTS...At 15.0 feet, Minor out of bank flooding will occur.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 9:45 PM CDT Sunday the stage was 16.2 feet.\n- Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage late\ntonight and continue falling to 4.5 feet Friday evening.\n- Bankfull stage is 15.0 feet.\n- Flood stage is 15.0 feet.",
        "instruction": "Do not drive cars through flooded areas. Caution is urged when\nwalking near riverbanks.\n\nAdditional information is available at water.noaa.gov/wfo/fwd.",
