        "headline": "Flood Warning issued June 7 at 9:59PM CDT until June 8 at 10:30PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX",
        "description": "...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Texas...\n\nTrinity River At Dallas affecting Dallas County.\n\nTrinity River Near Rosser affecting Ellis and Kaufman Counties.\n\nFor the Trinity River...including Dallas, Rosser, Trinidad, Long Lake\n(Oakwood)...Minor flooding is forecast.\n\n* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.\n\n* WHERE...Trinity River at Dallas.\n\n* WHEN...Until Monday evening.\n\n* IMPACTS...At 33.0 feet, Minor flooding along the river is expected.\nBike trails along the river will have floodwaters several feet\ndeep, and the parking lot of Trammel Crow Park beneath the Sylvan\nbridge will flood.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 9:30 PM CDT Sunday the stage was 32.8 feet.\n- Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 33.7 feet\njust after midnight tonight. It will then fall below flood stage\nlate tomorrow morning.\n- Bankfull stage is 30.0 feet.\n- Flood stage is 30.0 feet.",
        "instruction": "Do not drive cars through flooded areas. Caution is urged when\nwalking near riverbanks.\n\nAdditional information is available at water.noaa.gov/wfo/fwd.",
