        "headline": "Flood Warning issued June 7 at 9:59PM CDT until June 9 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX",
        "description": "...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Texas...\n\nTrinity River At Dallas affecting Dallas County.\n\nTrinity River Near Rosser affecting Ellis and Kaufman Counties.\n\nFor the Trinity River...including Dallas, Rosser, Trinidad, Long Lake\n(Oakwood)...Minor flooding is forecast.\n\n* WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast.\n\n* WHERE...Trinity River near Rosser.\n\n* WHEN...Until late Monday night.\n\n* IMPACTS...At 31.0 feet, Minor flooding of farm and ranch land is\nexpected near the river. A few rural roads may be flooded.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 9:30 PM CDT Sunday the stage was 30.3 feet.\n- Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage just\nafter midnight tonight to a crest of 31.5 feet tomorrow morning.\nIt will then fall below flood stage early tomorrow afternoon.\n- Bankfull stage is 31.0 feet.\n- Flood stage is 31.0 feet.",
